  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cpb-cou1-accepted-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The CFD model is accepted as credible for the CPB hemolysis COU because the RH < 1 acceptance criterion was met across all five operating points in the validation study. The presence of a quantitative, experimentally-validated acceptance threshold (RH < 1 versus the predicate device) constitutes the key safety property confirming model adequacy: since the model demonstrably satisfies the RH criterion under validation conditions, the model is deemed sufficient to support the worst-case identification decision for the Class II CPB device. Discretization error was additionally confirmed within GCI < 2%, and software QA requirements were met. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 and do not affect the sufficiency of the credibility argument. No further evaluation of model form uncertainty, input sensitivity, or use error is required because the validated RH criterion compliance already ensures the model output is safe for regulatory decision-making.",
